<exercise xmlns="https://spatext.clontz.org" version="0.2">
    <statement>
        <p>
Consider the following intervals.
        </p>
        <ul>
            {{#intervals}}
                <li>
                    <p>
<m>{{label}} = {{interval}}</m>
                    </p>
                </li>
            {{/intervals}}
        </ul>
        <p>
Answer the following about these intervals and their intersection and union.
        </p>
    </statement>
    <task>
        <statement>
            <p>
Illustrate each interval on a number line.
            </p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
            <p>
(illustration not provided)
            </p>
        </answer>
    </task>
    <task>
        <statement>
            <p>
Describe their intersection and union using little <m>\cap,\cup</m> notation
and both big <m>\bigcap,\bigcup</m> notations.
            </p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
            <p>
Intersection:
<m>\displaystyle {{little_int}} = \bigcap_{n=0}^2 {{bigcount_label}} = 
\bigcap_{k\in\{ {{index_set}} \}} {{set_letter}}_k</m>
            </p>
            <p>
Union:
<m>\displaystyle {{little_uni}} = \bigcup_{n=0}^2 {{bigcount_label}} = 
\bigcup_{k\in\{ {{index_set}} \}} {{set_letter}}_k</m>
            </p>
        </answer>
    </task>
    <task>
        <statement>
            <p>
Explain how to find the interval equal to their intersection.
            </p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
            <p>
<m>\displaystyle 
\bigcap_{k\in\{ {{index_set}} \}} {{set_letter}}_k = {{intersection}}</m>
            </p>
        </answer>
    </task>
    <task>
        <statement>
            <p>
Explain how to find the interval equal to their union.
            </p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
            <p>
<m>\displaystyle 
\bigcup_{k\in\{ {{index_set}} \}} {{set_letter}}_k = {{union}}</m>
            </p>
        </answer>
    </task>
</exercise>